Package model

Class AccessibilityGraph

java.lang.Object
model.AccessibilityGraph
public class AccessibilityGraph
extends java.lang.Object
Class that represents the (partial) accessibility graph of a petrinet. Provides functionality to build the graph both manually and automatically, and to analyse the graph's petrinet for unboundedness.
Author:
Alexander Steinberg

  • Constructor Details

    • AccessibilityGraph

      public AccessibilityGraph​(Petrinet petrinet)
      constructor for the accessibility graph. Sets the graph's petrinet, and initialises the graph with the current state of the petrinet.
      Parameters:
      petrinet - the graph's petrinet in its initial state

  • Method Details

    • addState

      public void addState​(Transition transition)
      Adds the current state of the petrinet to the accessibility graph. The transition provided must be the one that triggered the petrinet's update from the previous state.
      Parameters:
      transition - the transition that triggered the update from previous to current state of the graph's petrinet

    • getCurrentState

      public PetrinetState getCurrentState()
      get the state the petrinet is currently in.
      Returns:
      the most recent petrinet state

      public void clear()

    • getPetrinetStateById

      public PetrinetState getPetrinetStateById​(java.lang.String id)
      returns the petrinet state within the current accessibility graph that has the id, if it exists. Returns null otherwise.
      Parameters:
      id -
      Returns:
      the petrinet state with the id

    • getCurrentMAndMPrimeMessage

      public java.lang.String getCurrentMAndMPrimeMessage()
      gets a message that informs about the last discovered m and m' states. Returns null if none have been discovered.
      Returns:
      the string message that informs about the last discovered m and m' states, null if there are none

    • runAnalysis

      public void runAnalysis()
      checks whether there are m and m' in the current (partial) accessibility graph. If so, it sets the graph's m and m' state to them. Method is meant for on the fly analysis.

    • autoGenerate

      public void autoGenerate()
      Auto generates a (potentially partial) accessibility graph If the petrinet is bounded: generates the complete graph If the petrinet is unbounded: generates a partial accessibility graph with m and m'.

    • isUnbounded

      public boolean isUnbounded()
      If an analysis has revealed that the graph's petrinet is unbounded, this function returns true. Returns false otherwise.
      Returns:
      true if unboundedness has been detected for the petrinet, false otherwise

    • getInitialState

      public PetrinetState getInitialState()
      The function returns the initial state of the petrinet. This is either the state as it was loaded from file or the state set by the user when manually modifying the loaded petrinet.
      Returns:
      the accessibility graph's initial state

    • getInitialStateId

      public java.lang.String getInitialStateId()
      The function returns the id of the initial state of the petrinet. The intial state is either the state as it was loaded from file or the state set by the user when manually modifying the loaded petrinet.
      Returns:
      the id of the accessibility graph's initial state

    • getCurrentStateId

      public java.lang.String getCurrentStateId()
      The functino returns the id of the currently active petrinet state. The currently active petrinet state is either a) the initial state, b) the last state transitioned to or c) the state manually set to active by the user.
      Returns:
      the id of the currently active petrinet state

    • getPetrinetStates

      public java.util.Collection<PetrinetState> getPetrinetStates()
      Returns:
      the collection of petrinet states in the graph

    • getmStateId

      public java.lang.String getmStateId()
      Returns:
      the id of the currently found m state (a strictly smaller ancestor to some state in the graph)

    • getmPrimeStateId

      public java.lang.String getmPrimeStateId()
      Returns:
      the id of the currently found m' state (strictly greater than one of its ancestors)

    • getPathIds

      public java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> getPathIds()
      Constructs ids for all edges on the path from the initial state to the found mPrime state, if any. The ids are constructed via the getEdgeInfo function.
      Returns:
      the list of ids of edges on the path from the initial state to the currently found m' state

    • getPetrinetStateCount

      public int getPetrinetStateCount()
      Returns:
      the number of petrinet states in the graph

    • getEdgeCount

      public int getEdgeCount()
      Returns:
      the number of edges in the graph

    • getPathLength

      public int getPathLength()
      Returns:
      the length of the path from the initial state to the currently found m' state

    • getPathString

      public java.lang.String getPathString()
      If an unboundedness has been detected, this function returns a string representation of the path from the initial state to the found m' state. The representation has the form '([t1], ...[tn])'.
      Returns:
      a string that represents the path from the initial petrinet state to the currently found m' state

    • getmStateName

      public java.lang.String getmStateName()
      Returns:
      the name of the currently found m state

    • getmPrimeStateName

      public java.lang.String getmPrimeStateName()
      Returns:
      the name of the currently found m' state

    • getCurrentEdgeInfo

      public java.lang.String getCurrentEdgeInfo()
      The id is constructed via the getEdgeInfo function.
      Returns:
      a unique id for the current edge

    • getCurrentTransitionId

      public java.lang.String getCurrentTransitionId()
      get the id of the current transition, if any. The current transition is the transition that triggered the current state of the petrinet. If a user has manually set the petrinet to a certain state, the current transition is `null`.
      Returns:
      the id of the current transition, null if there is none.
